HEADWORD: Centre punch
<hw>Centre punch</hw> }</mhw>.
<fld>(Mech.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A punch for making indentations or
dots in a piece of work, as for suspension between lathe centers,
etc.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A punch for punching holes in sheet metal,
having a small conical center to insure correct locating.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

